<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Block 1 was the qualitative version. Today is quantitative.</p>
  <p>The energy-balance equation — solar input minus albedo-reflected, plus atmospheric trapping, equals thermal output — has a real numerical answer. Plug in the numbers: you get a planetary temperature. Plug in different greenhouse-gas concentrations: you get different temperatures. This is how climate science <em>predicts</em>. Not by hand-waving; by math.</p>
  <p>Today also connects directly back to <a href="/units/unit-1/">Unit 1</a>. The same energy-balance logic you'll work through here applies to Earth, Mars, and Venus in the <a href="/units/unit-1/assessment-goldilocks-report/">Goldilocks Report</a> habitability framework. Now you have the equations behind the framework — and the <a href="/units/unit-1/habitability-zone-calculator/">Habitability Zone Calculator</a> becomes a checkable model rather than a black box.</p>
</section>

